  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT287-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">piriviṭai vēṟupaṭṭa kiḻatti “nammait tuṟantu vārār” eṉṟu kavaṉṟāṭkup
          paruvam kāṭṭit tōḻi “varuvar” eṉac colliyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered in order to say “he is coming”, by the
          confidante while showing the season to her who was anxious “he has abandoned us [and]
          doesn't come!”, [namely] HER who had changed in the time of separation. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT287">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> amma vāḻi tōḻi kātala</l>
          <l> riṉṉē kaṇṭun tuṟakkuvar kollō</l>
          <l> munnāṟ ṟiṅka ṇiṟaipoṟut tacaii</l>
          <l> yotuṅkal cellāp pacumpuḷi vēṭkaik</l>
          <l> kaṭuñcūṉ makaḷir pōla nīrkoṇṭu</l>
          <l> vicumpivar kallātu tāṅkupu puṇaric</l>
          <l> ceḻumpal kuṉṟa nōkkip</l>
          <l> peruṅkali vāṉa mērtarum poḻutē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Alas, oh friend, [my] lover,</l>
          <l>will he give [me] up, even now that he has seen</l>
          <l rend="indent">the time when a big bustle is rising in the sky,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">facing the flourishing many hills,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">after [clouds] have united, bearing without being taught</l>
          <l rend="indent8">to climb the sky,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">with water, like women in heavy pregnancy</l>
          <l rend="indent3">demanding fresh, sour [things], unable to step aside ,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">wearied after having borne the fullness for twelve months ?</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
